-# Summary tab — matrix + sidebar. Substep coming in a follow-up; for
-# now render a coverage card so the page is meaningful.
.grid.gap-4{ class: "grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_320px]" }
  .rounded-lg.border.border-border.bg-bg-elev.p-5{ style: "box-shadow: var(--shadow-card-sm);" }
    %h3.font-semibold.text-fg.mb-2 Test × Computer matrix
    %p.text-fg-muted.text-sm.mb-4
      The cross-tab of every test case × every computer that submitted, with cell colors keyed to status and flags. Coming in a follow-up substep.
    .rounded-md.border.border-border-subtle.bg-bg-subtle.p-6.text-center.text-fg-subtle.text-sm
      = pluralize(@matrix.size, "test case")
      ·
      = pluralize(@per_computer.size, "computer")
      ·
      matrix data ready, rendering pending
  .space-y-4
    .rounded-lg.border.border-border.bg-bg-elev.p-4{ style: "box-shadow: var(--shadow-card-sm);" }
      %h3.font-semibold.text-fg.mb-2.flex.items-center.gap-2
        Computers
        %span.text-fg-subtle.tabular-nums{ class: "text-[11px]" }= "(#{@per_computer.size})"
      %ul.divide-y.divide-border-subtle
        - @per_computer.each do |row|
          %li.py-2.flex.items-center.justify-between.gap-2
            .flex.items-center.gap-2.min-w-0
              %span.inline-block.h-2.w-2.rounded-full.shrink-0{ class: status_dot_class_for_computer(row[:state]) }
              %span.font-mono.text-fg.truncate{ class: "text-[12px]" }
                = row[:computer]&.name || "computer ##{row[:computer_id]}"
            %span.font-mono.text-fg-muted.shrink-0{ class: "text-[11px]" }= summary_for_computer(row)
